You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for browsing operations.

BROWSE COMMANDS
  browse:      Open the repository in the browser


Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
The command opens the default web browser to the specified GitHub page.
Can navigate to specific branches, commits, and file paths.

Example usage:
- Open repo: GH_PAGER="" gh browse --repo <owner/repo>
- Open issue: GH_PAGER="" gh browse --repo <owner/repo> --issue <number>
- Open PR: GH_PAGER="" gh browse --repo <owner/repo> --pr <number>
- Open branch: GH_PAGER="" gh browse --repo <owner/repo> --branch <branch>
- Open file: GH_PAGER="" gh browse --repo <owner/repo> path/to/file 